The paper discusses the use of software-defined networking (SDN) in cellular and optical networks, which falls under the category of networked systems (cs.NI). The paper specifically focuses on the use of SDN in access backhaul network architecture, which involves the use of routing and scheduling algorithms, and the management of multiple operators, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO) and information theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses the performance of Distributed Converged Cable Access Platform (DCCAP) in cable architectures, which falls under the category of computer communications (cs.COMM) and distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC).
